4:["$","div",null,{"className":"rounded-2xl p-8 space-y-4","style":{"background":"var(--panel)","border":"1px solid var(--border)"},"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"The Premise"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-display)"},"children":"What If You Could Step Into Any World?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":["Every person carries within them a vast inner universe — and a quiet, persistent curiosity about what it would feel like to live inside someone else's. Fiction gets you partway there. Method acting gets you closer. But nothing quite puts you ",["$","em",null,{"children":"inside"}]," an experience the way a living, responsive, adaptive world can."]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":["Pandora's Box is an immersive reality engine. You step in. You choose a world. You inhabit a role — medieval king, deep-sea explorer, jazz musician in 1940s Harlem, a space captain navigating the politics of three civilizations. And then you ",["$","em",null,{"children":"live it"}],", with consequence, surprise, and the full weight of a world that responds to you."]}]]}]
5:["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-5","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"II. Why It Matters"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-display)"},"children":"Three Doors. One Box."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"Pandora's Box isn't just entertainment. It's a tool for the examined life — one that can unlock different things in different people."}]]}]
6:["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4 pl-0","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"Use Case I"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-display)"},"children":"The Big Effect — Be Careful What You Wish For"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":["In the film ",["$","em",null,{"children":"Big"}],", a twelve-year-old boy wishes to be big — and wakes up to discover that the life he wanted isn't quite what he imagined. The magic isn't the wish. The magic is what the wish teaches him about the life he already had."]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"Pandora's Box carries that same quiet gift. Step into the role of a king, and you might discover the loneliness at the top of the tower. Inhabit the life of someone with everything you think you want — and notice what you don't miss. Sometimes the fastest path to gratitude is the one that runs through someone else's door."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"The world you step into isn't an escape. It's a mirror."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"Use Case II"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-display)"},"children":"The Training Ground — Practice Makes Presence"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"Athletes run the play in their minds before they run it on the field. Great speakers rehearse the room before they walk into it. Performers live the character before the curtain rises. Repetition builds presence. And presence is confidence in motion."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"Pandora's Box is the ultimate training ground for anything you want to get better at — navigating conflict, holding authority, leading under pressure, communicating with grace, staying grounded when the stakes are high. You can walk into a room as a general who has already fought the battle. You can negotiate as someone who has already lived the outcome."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"The reps you put in here don't disappear when you close the session. They live in your body. Your intuition. Your calm."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"Use Case III"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-display)"},"children":"The Inner Journey — Navigating Your Own Universe"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"There is a version of this that goes deeper than entertainment, deeper than training — into the territory of the soul itself."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"Immersive experience, when it's crafted with intention, becomes a vehicle for inner work. You can step into a mythic world that mirrors an emotional truth you're living. You can inhabit a figure — a healer, a wanderer, a sage — and discover something true about yourself through their eyes. The metaphor gives you distance. The distance gives you clarity."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"Joseph Campbell called it the Hero's Journey: a departure from the known, a descent into the unknown, and a return with something you couldn't have found without leaving. Pandora's Box is a door for that journey. Not outward. Inward. Toward the magic of life that has always existed within you — waiting to be remembered."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-8","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"III. The People"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-display)"},"children":"The Founders"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-70","children":"Two builders who took the question seriously enough to do something about it."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"rounded-2xl overflow-hidden","style":{"background":"var(--panel)","border":"1px solid var(--border)"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"aspect-square relative overflow-hidden","children":["$","$L3",null,{"src":"/founders-binny.jpg","alt":"Binny Plotkin, Co-founder of Pandora's Box","fill":true,"className":"object-cover object-center"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"p-6 space-y-2","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-50","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"Co-founder"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-display)"},"children":"Binny Plotkin"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm leading-relaxed opacity-70","children":"Binny Plotkin is a builder and storyteller drawn to the intersection of technology, mythology, and the inner life. His work is rooted in the belief that within each person lives a vast inner infinity — and that the most powerful experiences are the ones that help us return to it. He approaches product development as a craft of meaning: technology, in his view, should disappear. What endures is the experience it leaves behind."}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"rounded-2xl overflow-hidden","style":{"background":"var(--panel)","border":"1px solid var(--border)"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"aspect-square relative overflow-hidden","children":["$","$L3",null,{"src":"/founders-josh.jpg","alt":"Josh Sassoon, Co-founder of Pandora's Box","fill":true,"className":"object-cover object-center"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"p-6 space-y-2","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-50","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"Co-founder"}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-display)"},"children":"Josh Sassoon"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm leading-relaxed opacity-70","children":"Josh Sassoon is a builder with an uncommon capacity to hold vision and execution in the same hand — to think with genuine philosophical depth while remaining sharply focused on what it takes to bring something real into the world. He has a rare instinct for identifying the questions worth asking, and the conviction to pursue them before the path is clear. Pandora's Box reflects both of those qualities."}]]}]]}]]}]]}]
a:["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"IV. The Moment"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-display)"},"children":"Why Now"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"The technology to do this well didn't exist until recently. Language models that can hold an entire world in memory, generate coherent consequence and dialogue, adapt to your choices in real time — all of that became possible in a window that spans roughly the last two years."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"The hunger for it is ancient. The tool is new. And we are standing at the exact moment where the two have finally met."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80","children":"The rock in Central Park was always there. It just took a while for the rest of the world to catch up to the conversation that happened on it."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"pt-8 text-center space-y-5 border-t","style":{"borderColor":"var(--border)"},"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg opacity-60 italic","children":["“The privilege of a lifetime is being who you are.”",["$","br",null,{}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-sm not-italic opacity-40","children":"— Joseph Campbell"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base opacity-60","children":"And sometimes — the quickest path back to yourself is the one that leads somewhere else first."}],["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/","className":"inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-sm font-medium transition-all hover:scale-105 hover:opacity-90","style":{"background":"var(--accent)","color":"#fff","fontFamily":"var(--font-mono)"},"children":"Open the Box →"}]]}]
